This paper is about language modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). The paper proposes a method based on compressed suffix trees, which is a data structure commonly used in string algorithms and falls under the computer science category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also discusses optimizations for improving query runtimes, which is a topic related to information retrieval (IR) and falls under the computer science category of "Information Retrieval" (cs.IR). The paper also presents results on memory usage and runtimes, which are topics related to machine learning (ML) and falls under the computer science category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG) and "Systems and Control" (cs.SD).
